}}{{TIDTOC|adapter}} ==Overview== May also be branded as a [[Dell WD518]]. Appears to be identical to the [[EDUP EP-N1557]] ([http://www.szedup.com/product-item/mini-usb-300mbps-wifi-adapter PPage]) as well. FCC photos show the device branded as EDUP.
{{FCC ST|04/11/2018|indexme.}} "YHMB8192EU-IN" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos.
The Realtek RTL8192EU chip ID comes from the RF Test Report doc which mentions "8192EU".
